  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Trimebutine acts through smooth muscle relaxation. It is presumed that the topical
      application of trimebutine after hemorrhoidectomy may help relieve pain after the procedure
      by relaxing the internal anal sphincter spasm.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A randomized trial will be carried out to investigate the effect of trimebutine on pain after
      Milligan-Morgan hemorrhoidectomy. Trimebutine relaxes the internal anal sphincter spasm which
      usually occurs after excisional hemorrhoidectomy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
