  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients of both genders aging between 18-70 years with grade III/VI internal
             hemorrhoids will be included

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with grade I/II internal hemorrhoids or external hemorrhoids.

          -  Patients with associated anorectal pathology such as anal fissure, anal fistula,
             rectal prolapse, neoplasm, solitary rectal ulcer, and inflammatory bowel diseases.\

          -  Patients with recurrent hemorrhoids after previous surgery.
      </textblock>
